<TITLE> German court jails three for juvenile prison murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERLIN, Oct 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A German court convicted three young men on Thursday of the sexual assault, torture and murder of a fellow inmate at a juvenile detention centre in a case that has caused widespread disquiet about such facilities. News of the gruesome crime forced the head of the Siegburg centre to resign and led to the government of North Rhine-Westphalia promising to undertake a reform of its facilities for minors. The state court in the western city of Bonn sentenced 20-year-old Pascal I. to 15 years in jail and 21-year-old Ralf A. to 14 years, court spokesman Thomas Stollenwerk said. He did not give their surnames. A 17-year-old was received a sentence of 10 years, the highest possible as he was tried as a minor. The three had previously confessed to raping their 20-year-old cellmate, Hermann H., and torturing him for almost 11 hours in November 2006. They then hanged him with torn-up bed sheets from a bathroom door in their cell. Prison wardens were unaware of what was happening and only found the body the next d
